The paper deals with algorithms for hypergraph matching, which is a problem in discrete mathematics and theoretical computer science. The use of linear programming and approximation algorithms suggests that the paper may belong to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) or cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics). The mention of bipartite hypergraphs and the improvement in approximation ratio suggests that the paper may also belong to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory). The use of the iterated packing method suggests that the paper may belong to cs.CC (Computational Complexity) or cs.IT (Information Theory).
